The paper deals with designing efficient encoders and decoders for quantum key distribution, which involves transmitting quantum bits over a noisy quantum channel. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes using machine learning techniques such as reinforcement learning and neural networks to design these encoders and decoders, which falls under the domains of quantum machine learning (cs.QL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with improving the performance of quantum codes, which falls under the domain of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes using deep Q-learning techniques, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
